WEBVTT

00:01.735 --> 00:03.170
TEDDY:
Hey, Julia, it's Teddy.

00:03.170 --> 00:05.305
My father was murdered.

00:05.305 --> 00:08.108
The person responsible said
that you and Paul were next.

00:18.619 --> 00:20.254
I can destroy you
just as easily as

00:20.254 --> 00:21.555
I could've killed you tonight.

00:21.555 --> 00:24.191
You head out,
slip our surveillance.

00:24.191 --> 00:25.759
Next time I see you,
I'll kill you.

00:25.759 --> 00:27.361
KANE:
Do you fish, Frankie?

00:27.361 --> 00:29.496
- No.
- Well, I do.

00:29.496 --> 00:31.632
And I caught something big.

00:31.632 --> 00:33.367
Come and see.

00:33.367 --> 00:36.036
FRANKLIN: Give up Buckley
and pray for a quick death.

00:36.036 --> 00:38.605
'Cause what these niggas
plan to do to you,

00:38.605 --> 00:40.440
why do that to yourself?

00:40.440 --> 00:41.708
JEROME:
Where the fuck she at?!

00:41.708 --> 00:43.577
You can kill me if you want to,

00:43.577 --> 00:45.712
or we can stop wasting time
and save your wife.

00:45.712 --> 00:47.347
JEROME:
Louie!

00:47.347 --> 00:49.283
(Louie crying)

00:55.422 --> 00:57.157
(grunts)

00:57.157 --> 01:00.260
(crying):
No... No!

01:00.260 --> 01:02.095
Jerome, don't leave me.

01:03.096 --> 01:04.298
Jerome.

01:09.570 --> 01:14.441
I need this done quick
and quietly,

01:14.441 --> 01:17.344
and without notifying
the police.

01:17.344 --> 01:18.712
Surely, Mr. Saint.

01:18.712 --> 01:21.215
I'll treat him
like I did my own father.

01:22.216 --> 01:25.185
Excuse me. (sighs)

01:29.456 --> 01:31.458
I'll take him.

01:42.469 --> 01:45.706
Wide. There we go.

01:48.275 --> 01:50.244
I'm-I'm so sorry, Mrs. Saint,

01:50.244 --> 01:53.413
but we have to be alone
with your husband for a while.

01:53.413 --> 01:54.414
But...

01:54.414 --> 01:56.250
Uh...

01:56.250 --> 01:58.051
in a day or two,
he'll be ready for you.

02:00.287 --> 02:01.588
Jerome.

02:01.588 --> 02:05.092
No, Jerome. Jerome!

02:05.092 --> 02:08.295
(crying):
Jerome! No, no, no, Jerome!

02:08.295 --> 02:10.230
Jerome.

02:10.230 --> 02:12.166
No, Jerome!

02:12.166 --> 02:15.369
Jerome, no, no, no, Jerome!

02:15.369 --> 02:17.371
(door closes)

02:17.371 --> 02:19.640
No, Jerome!

02:19.640 --> 02:21.742
Jerome! Jerome!

02:21.742 --> 02:24.344
No, get off me! No!

02:25.312 --> 02:28.081
No. No. No.

02:28.081 --> 02:30.150
(shouting indistinctly)

02:34.254 --> 02:36.290
♪ ♪

02:51.271 --> 02:53.307
(engine shuts off)

03:21.735 --> 03:23.971
(insects chirping)

03:34.448 --> 03:37.284
(keys jingling)

03:38.085 --> 03:40.387
LEON:
You want me to call
Buckley or somebody?

03:42.089 --> 03:44.091
LOUIE:
The war is over.

03:45.225 --> 03:47.261
Ain't it?

03:48.262 --> 03:50.998
I can stay if you want.

03:51.798 --> 03:54.034
No, you go ahead.

04:11.084 --> 04:12.586
(car door closes)

04:12.586 --> 04:14.655
(engine starts)

04:19.326 --> 04:21.361
(car departs)

04:26.500 --> 04:28.202
(cries softly)

04:37.211 --> 04:40.080
(panting)

04:42.082 --> 04:44.151
(crying)

05:00.100 --> 05:03.203
HAVEMEYER:
He went
into the Sherman Oaks Galleria,

05:03.203 --> 05:05.305
- parked, never came out.
- Okay.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.708
We know what he needs.

05:07.708 --> 05:10.077
He'll either surface again,
or he won't.

05:10.077 --> 05:12.212
Either way, we're fine.

05:12.212 --> 05:14.982
You call me
if you hear anything more.

05:20.654 --> 05:22.689
Problem?

05:26.026 --> 05:27.327
No.

05:27.327 --> 05:30.697
Okay. I have a question
for you, then.

05:30.697 --> 05:36.069
You have $73 million and
no food in your refrigerator?

05:36.069 --> 05:38.739
No decent furniture, no art,

05:38.739 --> 05:41.175
stained carpet, chipped paint.

05:41.175 --> 05:43.043
It's a rental.

05:43.043 --> 05:45.379
Oh. Okay.

05:45.379 --> 05:48.749
So, no actual house either.

05:49.750 --> 05:52.119
- For now.
- Hmm.

05:52.119 --> 05:53.320
(knocking)

06:04.731 --> 06:06.967
(knocking)

06:17.811 --> 06:19.479
Hey...

06:19.479 --> 06:21.114
Jules.

06:22.216 --> 06:24.051
Hey.

06:27.154 --> 06:29.389
Hey, Teddy.

06:30.357 --> 06:32.493
- Um...
- Julia.

06:38.465 --> 06:40.501
I didn't realize
the two of you had reconnected.

06:43.136 --> 06:47.574
When did that happen?

06:49.309 --> 06:51.345
Right.

06:54.781 --> 06:57.618
- Congratulations, by the way.
- Thank you.

06:57.618 --> 07:01.455
Uh, do you mind giving us
a minute, please, Parissa?

07:01.455 --> 07:03.690
She already knows everything.

07:10.264 --> 07:11.732
Okay.

07:13.534 --> 07:16.036
What happened?

07:16.036 --> 07:18.372
Why did your mule
kill your father?

07:18.372 --> 07:21.341
- He thinks I stole his money.
- Did you?

07:21.341 --> 07:23.043
I seized ill-gotten gains
on behalf

07:23.043 --> 07:24.745
of the United States government.

07:26.346 --> 07:28.649
(laughs)

07:28.649 --> 07:30.651
Wow.

07:30.651 --> 07:33.620
Okay, well, this is easy, then.

07:33.620 --> 07:35.022
Give it back.

07:35.022 --> 07:36.590
I can't.

07:38.792 --> 07:41.061
You haven't figured out yet
that the more you're worth,

07:41.061 --> 07:42.596
the more of a danger you are?

07:42.596 --> 07:44.464
You really think
I don't know that?

07:44.464 --> 07:47.367
I think if you did, you would
fucking walk away from this.

07:48.368 --> 07:50.037
But you won't.

07:50.037 --> 07:52.406
You'll double down
and tell yourself

07:52.406 --> 07:54.174
it's your-your patriotic duty.

07:54.174 --> 07:55.609
Shit, Teddy.

07:55.609 --> 07:57.611
(chuckles)

07:57.611 --> 08:00.280
But I know that's not
what's really driving you.

08:00.280 --> 08:02.783
And it's only gonna get worse

08:02.783 --> 08:04.384
now that he's dead.

08:05.385 --> 08:07.354
You ruined our family

08:07.354 --> 08:10.290
trying to prove something
to that tyrant.

08:12.259 --> 08:16.096
The only good thing
you ever gave me was our son.

08:18.098 --> 08:20.467
And now
you're trying to kill him.

08:22.503 --> 08:25.439
Give Franklin back the money, Teddy.

08:26.440 --> 08:29.009
Fix this...

08:29.009 --> 08:31.011
or I will fix it for you.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.313
TEDDY:
How are you gonna fix it for me?

08:34.348 --> 08:37.217
A public execution.

08:39.253 --> 08:41.288
(footsteps retreating)

08:45.726 --> 08:47.528
(knocking)

08:51.632 --> 08:53.433
Franklin.

08:53.433 --> 08:56.103
FRANKLIN:
Wanda.

08:56.103 --> 08:58.038
(door closes)

08:58.038 --> 09:00.107
WANDA:
Where's Leon?

09:00.107 --> 09:02.376
Uh, he said he might be late.

09:02.376 --> 09:04.444
He's gonna drop Louie home.

09:05.412 --> 09:07.514
Okay.

09:12.553 --> 09:14.721
Leon is with Louie?

09:16.757 --> 09:19.226
Yes.

09:21.228 --> 09:23.263
And Jerome?

09:52.726 --> 09:54.962
♪ ♪

10:07.074 --> 10:08.976
Did he suffer?

10:12.379 --> 10:14.214
No.

10:41.475 --> 10:45.445
I've always thought Julia was
a bitch with a log up her ass,

10:45.445 --> 10:47.514
but she has a point.

10:47.514 --> 10:50.117
(coffee dripping)

10:50.117 --> 10:52.519
(Teddy sighs)

10:55.756 --> 10:58.292
You really don't think
that if my son was in danger,

10:58.292 --> 11:00.394
I would do something
to protect him?

11:02.429 --> 11:05.632
Honestly... I don't know.

11:07.134 --> 11:08.602
They're fine.

11:10.204 --> 11:11.538
They're protected.

11:14.708 --> 11:19.479
You believe you have nothing to
fear from anyone but your own.

11:21.815 --> 11:24.484
I believe that that money...

11:26.286 --> 11:28.288
...belongs to us.

11:31.458 --> 11:33.760
Belongs to us?

11:33.760 --> 11:36.763
It belongs to you.

11:36.763 --> 11:40.000
Or were you planning
on giving me half of it?

11:42.302 --> 11:44.505
Is that what you want?

11:50.344 --> 11:53.614
Teddy, I care about you.

11:54.615 --> 11:56.717
You're fierce

11:56.717 --> 11:59.019
and ambitious.

11:59.820 --> 12:03.790
But I'm not in this
to just tag along.

12:03.790 --> 12:06.393
I'm at risk, too.

12:07.427 --> 12:10.230
If I don't have a purpose,

12:10.230 --> 12:13.300
I am going to get very bored

12:13.300 --> 12:16.403
and go looking for it elsewhere.

12:18.405 --> 12:21.475
I'm giving you the keys
to my lock.

12:22.476 --> 12:25.245
You should use them.

12:43.597 --> 12:46.200
(knocking)

13:10.290 --> 13:11.959
Cissy.

13:15.596 --> 13:17.998
You, uh...

13:19.066 --> 13:20.534
You want to come in?

13:22.703 --> 13:24.404
Yeah.

13:30.477 --> 13:32.613
Jerome loved you.

13:36.149 --> 13:40.721
I never seen him as much as make
a passing nod to another women,

13:40.721 --> 13:42.723
even the ones he was with.

13:42.723 --> 13:46.193
But he loved you.

13:47.561 --> 13:49.696
It's gonna be all I can do

13:49.696 --> 13:52.399
to not climb down
in that grave with him.

13:59.606 --> 14:01.675
This has to stop.

14:05.445 --> 14:07.481
With us.

14:17.057 --> 14:19.026
All of this

14:19.026 --> 14:21.628
is Franklin's fault.

14:22.429 --> 14:26.166
He certainly did
his share,
but we all played a part.

14:26.166 --> 14:28.268
- Hmm.
- Between the money

14:28.268 --> 14:30.304
and the white man and his war...

14:30.304 --> 14:32.306
Hmm. Mm-hmm.

14:32.306 --> 14:34.441
...ain't no one going home
with clean hands.

14:34.441 --> 14:37.778
No, but I'm the one
who lost my husband,

14:37.778 --> 14:40.380
my whole fucking world.

14:40.380 --> 14:42.382
I lost him, too,

14:42.382 --> 14:45.419
and my husband.

14:48.288 --> 14:50.290
I don't want
to lose anyone else.

14:53.060 --> 14:55.128
I understand.

14:55.929 --> 14:59.099
You still got things
you care about.

15:01.468 --> 15:03.504
I don't.

15:09.209 --> 15:11.578
Go get the guys and take that
to the cookhouse.

15:11.578 --> 15:15.282
(man speaking indistinctly
on radio)

15:30.030 --> 15:32.699
What's my credit line, Lee?

15:32.699 --> 15:35.202
As good as my life.

15:36.737 --> 15:40.240
Look, um, I need a favor.

15:42.042 --> 15:44.111
I need half a million.

15:44.912 --> 15:47.648
And I'm
not sure
when I can get it back to you.

15:47.648 --> 15:49.550
What's it for?

15:50.551 --> 15:52.986
The price of freedom.

15:54.454 --> 15:56.590
(indistinct chatter)

15:56.590 --> 15:59.560
Still can't believe he gone.

15:59.560 --> 16:01.695
He was forever, you know?

16:01.695 --> 16:04.665
Could never really imagine
him not being there.

16:04.665 --> 16:06.967
Still can't.

16:08.335 --> 16:12.005
We all
on the killing floor, Lee.

16:12.005 --> 16:14.608
Shit could have happened
to anybody.

16:17.678 --> 16:19.646
Look,

16:19.646 --> 16:23.183
he was my blood, all right?

16:23.183 --> 16:25.385
And I loved him.

16:25.385 --> 16:28.155
But he never should have
broke away from us.

16:31.458 --> 16:33.594
None of this shit
ever should've happened.

16:37.297 --> 16:39.166
Look, I'll be back tomorrow
to get the cash,

16:39.166 --> 16:40.501
if it's all right.

16:42.202 --> 16:44.171
(quietly):
Yeah.

16:44.171 --> 16:46.306
Thanks, Lee.

16:46.306 --> 16:48.208
I owe you.

16:52.746 --> 16:56.283
(kisses, laughs)

16:59.553 --> 17:01.255
- (gunshot)
- (gasps softly)

17:01.255 --> 17:02.789
- (bullet casing clinks)
- LOUIE: No!

17:02.789 --> 17:05.092
Jerome, hey, hey.

17:05.092 --> 17:06.426
No!

17:06.426 --> 17:07.761
Wake up!

17:07.761 --> 17:08.996
(screams)

17:10.030 --> 17:11.398
(gasps)

17:14.034 --> 17:16.003
(panting)

17:18.605 --> 17:20.674
(glass breaks)

17:25.179 --> 17:26.547
(grunts)

17:26.547 --> 17:29.082
(panting)

17:33.687 --> 17:36.023
Fuck!

17:41.528 --> 17:44.031
No!

17:44.031 --> 17:45.566
Fuck you!

17:45.566 --> 17:48.702
(crying)

17:48.702 --> 17:51.405
(groaning)

17:55.275 --> 17:59.012
Fuck you! Fuck you!

17:59.012 --> 18:00.214
(tires screech)

18:02.749 --> 18:04.251
What the fuck is wrong with you?

18:04.251 --> 18:05.786
- You crazy, bitch?
- LOUIE: Shoot me, nigga.

18:05.786 --> 18:08.188
Shoot me, little nigga!

18:08.188 --> 18:09.723
- What the fuck you waiting for?
- GUARD: Yo, what the fuck
happening here?

18:09.723 --> 18:11.425
- GUARD 2: Chill out.
- Motherfucker. Skully!

18:11.425 --> 18:13.227
Man, calm your asses down.
That's Louie Saint.

18:13.227 --> 18:15.028
Watch out, nigga. Get the
fuck... Oh, you gonna push me?

18:15.028 --> 18:18.165
Come on, then, nigga.
You want to get me, come on.

18:18.165 --> 18:19.566
Shoot the fucking gun. Skully!

18:19.566 --> 18:21.401
Get your niggas!

18:21.401 --> 18:23.170
Why you still standing there, nigga?

18:23.170 --> 18:24.538
Shoot the fucking gun!

18:24.538 --> 18:26.707
(knocks on door)

18:26.707 --> 18:28.575
What the fuck you...?

18:28.575 --> 18:31.378
Man, she drove up on the curb
and started cussing at Koko.

18:31.378 --> 18:33.380
SKULLY:
Look, man, y'all go.

18:33.380 --> 18:35.415
Come on, Ms. Saint.

18:36.750 --> 18:39.019
Go, man.

18:50.664 --> 18:53.100
Mama, what's wrong?

18:53.100 --> 18:56.570
You said I could come
if I wanted.

18:56.570 --> 18:59.540
Of course. Have a seat.

19:04.578 --> 19:06.480
Just a little...

19:16.623 --> 19:18.458
(Louie groans softly)

19:23.730 --> 19:25.999
How'd you do it?

19:27.534 --> 19:29.570
Do what?

19:29.570 --> 19:32.639
Keep peace in your heart

19:32.639 --> 19:37.477
after your girl
and your baby was killed.

19:39.213 --> 19:41.415
'Cause I know they're not gone.

19:44.484 --> 19:47.521
And I don't want
to taint the love we have.

19:47.521 --> 19:50.057
But ain't...

19:50.057 --> 19:53.560
ain't you so mad, you want
to burn this fucking house down?

19:53.560 --> 19:56.029
Hell yeah.

19:56.029 --> 19:58.265
All the time.

20:01.568 --> 20:04.238
But they won't let me.

20:20.087 --> 20:23.357
(Franklin groaning)

20:23.357 --> 20:25.392
(Veronique grunts)

20:28.562 --> 20:32.432
Franklin. Franklin.

20:32.432 --> 20:34.334
Franklin. Franklin!

20:34.334 --> 20:36.203
- (screaming)
- Wake up. Wake up.

20:36.203 --> 20:38.705
Wake up! Wake up.
Wait, no, no, no, no!

20:38.705 --> 20:41.008
No, no, no, no. It was a dream.
It was a dream. You're dreaming.

20:41.008 --> 20:43.143
- (whimpering)
- You're dreaming, okay?
You're dreaming. Stop.

20:43.143 --> 20:45.179
- Stop, stop, stop. Hey.
- I can't breathe.

20:45.179 --> 20:47.181
Calm down. Come here.

20:47.181 --> 20:49.716
- Aah! I can't fucking breathe!
- You got to calm down, hey.

20:49.716 --> 20:51.718
- Hey, what's happening to you?
- (whimpering)

20:51.718 --> 20:53.320
Has this happened to you before?

20:53.320 --> 20:56.089
- I don't know. One-- once maybe.
- Okay. Okay.

20:56.089 --> 20:58.292
- (groans)
- I'm here. Come here, come here.

20:58.292 --> 21:00.503
You're all right. You're fine.

21:00.503 --> 21:02.905
Listen to me.
You're-you're alive.

21:02.905 --> 21:05.908
You're-you're safe.
You're with me, okay?

21:05.908 --> 21:07.810
- Okay.
- What the fuck is
happening to me?

21:07.810 --> 21:09.912
Nothing.
Nothing, nothing, nothing.

21:09.912 --> 21:11.914
Nothing. There is a plan,

21:11.914 --> 21:13.883
and we're carrying out
that plan.

21:13.883 --> 21:16.652
There's nothing wrong with you,
you hear me? You're fine.

21:16.652 --> 21:18.788
You're fine. You're fine.

21:18.788 --> 21:20.790
(voice breaking):
You're fine.

21:20.790 --> 21:22.091
I'm not fine.

21:22.091 --> 21:25.027
(panting)

21:41.544 --> 21:43.512
(car door closes)

21:45.815 --> 21:47.783
Oh, Egypt.

21:48.784 --> 21:51.620
(both crying)

21:53.789 --> 21:56.959
CANDY:
I got you. I got you.

21:56.959 --> 22:00.629
- I got you. I got you.
- (crying)

22:04.634 --> 22:06.636
(clattering)

22:08.537 --> 22:10.606
(Xiamara sighs heavily)

22:13.109 --> 22:15.478
- It's your turn.
- Oh.

22:16.946 --> 22:18.614
(Xiamara sighs)

22:23.085 --> 22:25.021
(Gustavo groans softly)

22:26.055 --> 22:28.157
(door opens)

23:08.564 --> 23:09.665
Ah.

23:11.567 --> 23:15.004
- What the fuck is this?
- No.

23:16.572 --> 23:18.040
I'm a friend.

23:18.040 --> 23:20.509
A friend with a gun
at my kitchen table?

23:30.219 --> 23:33.055
...we'll need to get away.

24:08.958 --> 24:10.159
Ah.

24:34.950 --> 24:36.752
(mutters)

24:40.189 --> 24:42.992
- (lock clicks)
- (Xiamara sighs)

24:45.227 --> 24:47.463
This is too much.

24:48.230 --> 24:50.499
I know.

24:51.500 --> 24:54.036
Maybe this should be the end...

24:54.036 --> 24:55.471
for us.

25:01.510 --> 25:04.613
Maybe you shouldn't know
where we go.

25:05.581 --> 25:07.616
Yeah, maybe.

25:10.219 --> 25:11.787
(footsteps rapidly retreating)

25:11.787 --> 25:15.091
(sighs)

25:15.091 --> 25:17.159
(sportscaster speaking
indistinctly on radio)

25:20.696 --> 25:24.033
(lock clicks, keys jingle)

25:25.801 --> 25:27.937
Oh, you're here. Dope.

25:27.937 --> 25:30.640
Thank you.
It felt like time.

25:30.640 --> 25:33.643
Yeah. What's all that?

25:33.643 --> 25:36.212
Everything I'm gonna need
for my new place.

25:36.212 --> 25:37.880
You leaving me?

25:37.880 --> 25:40.049
(laughs)
No, Lee.

25:42.852 --> 25:45.187
But I'm leaving the PJs.

25:45.187 --> 25:47.490
Well, goddamn,
we gonna talk about it?

25:47.490 --> 25:51.027
We gonna talk about those guns?

25:51.027 --> 25:54.196
Lee, look.

25:54.196 --> 25:58.734
In a perfect world, I'd be
out of here today, right now.

25:58.734 --> 26:01.504
Head to Ghana with my husband.

26:01.504 --> 26:05.041
We could raise a family there,
a house full of kids.

26:05.041 --> 26:08.210
But instead you sitting here,
getting ready for war?

26:08.210 --> 26:11.180
- Baby, we've been through this.
- We have.

26:11.180 --> 26:14.550
But...

26:14.550 --> 26:16.552
all I see

26:16.552 --> 26:21.190
is us headed to the same grave
Jerome gonna get.

26:22.024 --> 26:26.762
I see it,
and I'm about ready
to change direction.

26:26.762 --> 26:30.499
Look, I just need
to straighten some things out.

26:30.499 --> 26:32.902
Then I can pass the PJs on
to the next man.

26:32.902 --> 26:35.705
I wish I could believe that, Lee.

26:38.808 --> 26:40.509
(kisses)

26:56.826 --> 27:00.696
You remember
Danielle's older brother?

27:00.696 --> 27:02.698
- Ronald?
- Yeah.

27:02.698 --> 27:05.468
Remember he paid us $20
to see how long

27:05.468 --> 27:07.536
- he could strangle us
before we passed out?
- (laughs)

27:07.536 --> 27:12.041
Yeah. I saw you,
and I knew, "Don't do it,"

27:12.041 --> 27:13.909
but it was $20.

27:13.909 --> 27:16.012
(both laugh)

27:19.815 --> 27:22.051
Every time my throat would do
that whistle thing, I...

27:22.051 --> 27:25.788
I'd just flash right back
to that.

27:25.788 --> 27:28.791
- Right.
- And then it just...

27:28.791 --> 27:31.661
and then it just got
more and more.

27:31.661 --> 27:36.532
Like when Keith and 'em
locked us down in the basement

27:36.532 --> 27:38.134
with my Uncle Quick?

27:40.970 --> 27:43.139
Like Lawrence and his brothers.

27:47.109 --> 27:49.612
(voice breaking):
But a thousand times worse.

27:51.580 --> 27:55.484
I did everything
to get myself out of that,

27:55.484 --> 27:57.953
and then, bam,
there I go, right back.

27:57.953 --> 28:01.490
Louie, you know
this wasn't your fault.

28:01.490 --> 28:03.059
It ain't?

28:03.059 --> 28:05.728
How the fuck did I get here?
Again?

28:08.831 --> 28:11.901
(sighs)
Now I lost Jerome.

28:12.935 --> 28:15.004
And the worst part?

28:17.573 --> 28:20.609
I keep forgetting he died.

28:23.579 --> 28:25.614
(pager chiming, buzzing)

28:30.987 --> 28:33.622
Yeah...

28:40.062 --> 28:43.499
Oh, this nigga.

28:45.234 --> 28:47.470
(phone ringing)

28:49.572 --> 28:51.741
- Louie?
- What do you want?

28:51.741 --> 28:53.175
Excuse me?

28:53.175 --> 28:54.777
What...

28:54.777 --> 28:57.480
do you want with me?

28:57.480 --> 28:59.515
I've been paging you.

28:59.515 --> 29:01.617
Yeah,
and I haven't called you back,

29:01.617 --> 29:03.619
so that must mean that I'm busy.

29:03.619 --> 29:04.920
Busy or dead.

29:04.920 --> 29:06.622
Busy doing what?

29:06.622 --> 29:08.624
Excuse you, Mr. White Man,

29:08.624 --> 29:10.626
but if I say I'm busy,
it means I'm fucking busy.

29:10.626 --> 29:12.662
This isn't a request.

29:18.100 --> 29:20.770
Louie.

29:20.770 --> 29:22.438
I heard you.

29:23.939 --> 29:25.908
I can meet you

29:25.908 --> 29:30.179
over at that Fosters
parking lot at 3:00.

29:30.179 --> 29:31.814
I need to see you now.

29:31.814 --> 29:33.482
I'll see you then.

29:38.087 --> 29:41.123
- (siren wailing)
- (dogs barking)

29:44.060 --> 29:47.063
I heard you were leaving us.

29:47.063 --> 29:50.066
I think I have to.

29:51.968 --> 29:54.103
I understand.

29:59.909 --> 30:02.878
Well, if you need an apartment,

30:02.878 --> 30:07.183
I'm sure there's one
at one of our buildings.

30:07.183 --> 30:09.051
Uh, for real?

30:09.051 --> 30:10.920
Mm-hmm.

30:10.920 --> 30:13.990
You've already done so much
for me, though, Ms. Saint.

30:14.957 --> 30:17.159
- Thank you.
- It's nothing.

30:22.231 --> 30:24.934
What about taking over
my position

30:24.934 --> 30:27.103
at the shelter full-time?

30:31.240 --> 30:33.909
I-I don't know what to say.

30:33.909 --> 30:36.012
Say yes.

30:37.213 --> 30:39.482
You'd be doing me a favor.

30:43.519 --> 30:46.155
I can't be there right now.

30:48.190 --> 30:51.193
I don't think
I'll ever be there again.

30:52.695 --> 30:54.764
Really?

30:56.699 --> 30:58.734
What would you do then?

31:00.836 --> 31:03.839
I mean, like,
when all this is over?

31:15.051 --> 31:16.886
(engine shuts off)

31:18.688 --> 31:20.656
Oso!

31:20.656 --> 31:22.758
What's up, man?

31:25.127 --> 31:27.096
No more waiting, moreno.

31:27.096 --> 31:28.764
We're moving tomorrow.

31:28.764 --> 31:30.533
I need the documents
and the money now.

31:30.533 --> 31:32.168
Well, yeah, I got the money,
but the documents--

31:32.168 --> 31:34.003
they take what they take.

31:38.074 --> 31:39.809
(Gustavo yells)

31:39.809 --> 31:42.678
Oso, what the fuck happened?

31:42.678 --> 31:44.613
(sighing)

31:51.053 --> 31:53.656
I need your help
because the DEA busted me.

31:53.656 --> 31:55.725
What?

31:57.193 --> 31:59.228
They took all my money
and forced me to help them.

31:59.228 --> 32:01.964
Help them with what?

32:01.964 --> 32:05.501
They want Teddy.
Wanted you, too.

32:05.501 --> 32:08.137
Oso, what the fuck, man?!

32:08.137 --> 32:10.039
How long
you been talking to 'em?

32:10.039 --> 32:11.907
They got me just after you left.

32:11.907 --> 32:15.211
They have photos of Louie.

32:15.211 --> 32:19.181
But you're clean, moreno,
I swear.

32:22.852 --> 32:24.820
Jesus fucking Christ.

32:24.820 --> 32:26.922
It's not only them.

32:26.922 --> 32:29.492
You remember that picture
I showed you?

32:29.492 --> 32:31.560
You knew he was KGB, right?

32:31.560 --> 32:34.163
Yeah. What about him?

32:34.163 --> 32:35.931
He came at me, too.

32:35.931 --> 32:38.768
Broke into my house,
threatened my family.

32:42.171 --> 32:46.475
Listen, they want Teddy.

32:47.276 --> 32:50.513
Two days from now, t
hey want
his cocaine in the warehouse.

32:50.513 --> 32:52.515
Oh, yeah?

32:52.515 --> 32:54.116
And Ruben plans
to kill him there?

32:56.519 --> 32:58.487
I don't think so.

32:58.487 --> 33:00.489
He knows about the DEA,

33:00.489 --> 33:04.527
and I guess
he wants them to arrest him.

33:04.527 --> 33:06.529
But the DEA guy--
he's getting frustrated,

33:06.529 --> 33:09.799
and he's about to pull the plug
and take me to jail.

33:09.799 --> 33:11.667
So everybody wants Teddy, huh?

33:11.667 --> 33:15.137
DEA, KGB and me?

33:15.137 --> 33:16.739
Yes.

33:17.773 --> 33:19.909
And I'm
at the fucking crossroad.

33:21.911 --> 33:26.182
So, if you want him,
it needs to happen now, moreno.

33:27.216 --> 33:29.185
Like this.

33:35.958 --> 33:37.760
Fine.

33:38.561 --> 33:41.897
Think I know a way
to buy you
another day with the DEA.

33:41.897 --> 33:46.802
But, Oso, listen to me
very fucking carefully.

33:46.802 --> 33:50.740
I need Teddy, and I need him
right fucking now.

33:54.210 --> 33:56.679
Yeah, I haven't seen him
in days,

33:56.679 --> 33:59.015
since you killed his father.

33:59.782 --> 34:03.185
Motherfucker
's hiding
like a cat hunting a bird.

34:06.222 --> 34:08.624
But lucky for us, I'm that bird.

34:09.659 --> 34:11.494
Teddy's no pinche cat.

34:11.494 --> 34:15.064
He will smell a trap, you know.

34:15.064 --> 34:17.199
Yeah, you're right about that.

34:17.199 --> 34:19.635
You're just gonna have
to make him believe

34:19.635 --> 34:21.704
it was him that set me up.

34:23.806 --> 34:25.841
Right?

34:27.677 --> 34:29.812
(Gustavo sighs heavily)

34:29.812 --> 34:32.181
I'm sorry, moreno.

34:38.254 --> 34:41.023
You did what you had to do.

34:41.791 --> 34:43.926
<i>HA</i>
VEMEYER:
<i>He's definitely losing it.</i>

34:43.926 --> 34:46.829
The kid actually found
his old man and murdered him

34:46.829 --> 34:48.931
while on the phone with Teddy.

34:48.931 --> 34:51.200
The nigger murdered his father?

34:51.200 --> 34:53.936
- Just cut his fucking throat.
- (groans)

34:53.936 --> 34:55.938
Teddy could hear him choking
on his own blood.

34:55.938 --> 34:57.940
Oh, Jesus.

34:57.940 --> 35:00.776
(both sigh)

35:00.776 --> 35:03.879
I like Teddy.

35:03.879 --> 35:06.515
He's no bleeding heart,
and he was a patriot.

35:07.984 --> 35:10.786
Since he's been on this mission,
he's gotten ambitious.

35:10.786 --> 35:13.489
- The money he stole
could be useful.
- Yeah.

35:13.489 --> 35:14.924
And the business
still has potential.

35:14.924 --> 35:16.192
I don't want to know anything
about all that.

35:16.192 --> 35:17.760
That's your business.

35:17.760 --> 35:20.062
Everything is problematic.

35:20.062 --> 35:23.165
Especially
when you add in the KGB.

35:23.165 --> 35:25.601
They want to put us
on the nightly news.

35:26.402 --> 35:31.140
Sounds like you
got some cracks
to fill, so fill 'em.

35:32.108 --> 35:34.076
(Witherspoon sighs)

35:34.076 --> 35:36.479
- (footsteps retreating)
- (Havemeyer sighs)

35:40.816 --> 35:42.852
(indistinct chatter)

35:48.557 --> 35:50.192
(car engine shuts off)

35:57.133 --> 35:59.068
What happened?

35:59.068 --> 36:01.170
Business disagreement.
What you need?

36:02.204 --> 36:03.739
Franklin.

36:04.774 --> 36:06.008
Why?

36:06.976 --> 36:08.744
'Cause he murdered my father.

36:10.780 --> 36:12.815
So all you got to do is point.

36:12.815 --> 36:15.184
Me and Franklin don't socialize.

36:15.184 --> 36:16.752
I need you to fix that.

36:16.752 --> 36:18.521
Fuck you.

36:18.521 --> 36:21.223
Don't forget that you work
for me, you sell my drugs.

36:21.223 --> 36:23.959
You make a lot of fucking money.

36:23.959 --> 36:27.496
All I'm asking for is Franklin.

36:32.835 --> 36:34.804
Tomorrow...

36:34.804 --> 36:38.174
I put my husband in the ground,

36:38.174 --> 36:40.176
and I got Franklin
to thank for that.

36:40.176 --> 36:42.178
Jerome's dead?

36:43.779 --> 36:45.481
That's right.

36:47.683 --> 36:48.918
(sighs)

36:48.918 --> 36:50.920
So,

36:50.920 --> 36:54.657
seems like you and me--
we got something in common.

36:56.692 --> 36:58.194
After the funeral,

36:58.194 --> 36:59.929
I'll do whatever the fuck
you want me to do--

36:59.929 --> 37:03.065
slit Franklin neck to nuts,
if I get the chance.

37:03.065 --> 37:05.167
Until then,

37:05.167 --> 37:07.837
leave me alone.

37:17.046 --> 37:19.482
(engine starts)

37:24.987 --> 37:27.890
("Boadicea" by Enya
playing)

37:32.828 --> 37:35.131
(singer vocalizing)

38:01.557 --> 38:03.626
♪ ♪

38:13.669 --> 38:16.605
I think about Jerome

38:16.605 --> 38:19.208
and how sweet he was,

38:19.208 --> 38:23.045
how much everybody says
he loved Louie.

38:26.215 --> 38:28.617
And I can't help but think
about losing you.

38:28.617 --> 38:32.154
Well, I'm right here with you,
Mrs. Simmons.

38:33.789 --> 38:35.157
Yeah.

38:38.928 --> 38:40.162
Yeah.

38:40.963 --> 38:44.734
But just a few days ag
o, Jerome
was right there with Louie.

38:46.102 --> 38:48.771
I'm scared, Lee.

39:05.988 --> 39:07.723
The fuck was that?

39:09.659 --> 39:11.093
(crowd murmuring)

39:11.093 --> 39:13.596
Y'all may pay y'all respect
to the Saint family.

39:18.701 --> 39:21.037
- Oso.
- Hey.

39:21.037 --> 39:23.172
Sorry for your loss, amigo.

39:23.172 --> 39:25.174
(speaks Spanish)

39:25.174 --> 39:27.476
Uh-huh.

39:27.476 --> 39:29.779
Listen,
I've got some good news for you.

39:29.779 --> 39:31.914
Make sure you come
to the repast after.

39:31.914 --> 39:33.983
We'll talk there. All right?

39:46.829 --> 39:49.165
I'm sorry, baby.

40:02.578 --> 40:04.613
Louie, um...

40:06.682 --> 40:08.751
I'm-I'm so sorry.

40:10.186 --> 40:12.154
He didn't page you?

40:12.154 --> 40:14.190
Ask for your gun
at the junkyard?

40:16.826 --> 40:18.160
Nah.

40:21.597 --> 40:23.599
All right.

40:38.914 --> 40:41.183
♪ Pass me not ♪

40:41.183 --> 40:48.190
♪ O gentle Savior ♪

40:48.190 --> 40:54.530
♪ Hear my humble cry... ♪

40:54.530 --> 40:56.899
MINISTER:
Jesus and his hallowed Father

40:56.899 --> 40:59.535
work in mysterious ways.

40:59.535 --> 41:02.004
But today is no mystery.

41:02.004 --> 41:04.774
♪ Thou art smiling... ♪

41:04.774 --> 41:08.611
Too often I have blamed
these deaths

41:08.611 --> 41:10.513
on young men with guns.

41:10.513 --> 41:15.217
♪ Help my unbelief... ♪

41:15.217 --> 41:17.486
Today I finally understand

41:17.486 --> 41:20.189
that all the rest of us
are guilty, too.

41:20.189 --> 41:23.059
♪ Savior... ♪

41:23.059 --> 41:26.162
And it's not just us.

41:26.162 --> 41:29.098
It's the church leaders,
the city council,

41:29.098 --> 41:32.802
and the millionaires have all
brought this pain

41:32.802 --> 41:34.070
to our streets.

41:34.070 --> 41:36.505
Our people are suffering.

41:36.505 --> 41:39.675
And we have not done
near enough to succor them.

41:39.675 --> 41:46.749
♪ Do not pass me by. ♪

41:55.191 --> 41:57.059
MAN:
Excuse me.

41:59.695 --> 42:00.896
Hey, nigga.

42:06.702 --> 42:09.605
You gonna kill the motherfuckers
that did that to Rome?

42:15.177 --> 42:17.146
All right.

42:45.541 --> 42:48.010
FRANKLIN:
What you need from me, Auntie?

42:50.079 --> 42:52.848
I need you to answer
a question for me.

42:53.816 --> 42:55.151
What's that?

42:58.721 --> 43:00.756
Why'd you come back for me?

43:09.065 --> 43:11.901
I was raised to respect women,
you know?

43:14.971 --> 43:16.906
It's a man's duty.

43:18.975 --> 43:21.010
And there's no way
I could have lived with myself

43:21.010 --> 43:23.145
if I left you there with Kane.

43:26.949 --> 43:28.751
That it?

43:28.751 --> 43:30.119
No.

43:32.221 --> 43:34.056
No, no, no, no, no.

43:34.056 --> 43:38.494
You made me a promise
in that warehouse.

43:42.965 --> 43:46.002
I need all the help I can get.

43:50.039 --> 43:52.141
You are the devil.

43:53.175 --> 43:54.910
You know that?

43:54.910 --> 43:57.780
("My People... Hold On"
by Eddie Kendricks playing)

44:02.051 --> 44:03.786
Yeah.

44:06.255 --> 44:08.491
I know.

